escript\ninterface SiteConfig {\n  title: string;\n  baseUrl: string;\n  outputDir: string;\n  contentDir: string;\n  templateDir: string;\n}\n```\n\n### `ContentFile`\n```typescript\ninterface ContentFile {\n  slug: string;\n  title: string;\n  content: string;        // raw content (markdown or html)\n  metadata: Record<string, unknown>;\n  date?: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n  template?: string;\n}\n```\n\n### `BuildContext`\n```typescript\ninterface BuildContext {\n  config: SiteConfig;\n  files: ContentFile[];\n  output: Map<string, string>;  // output path -> rendered content\n  assets: Map<string, Buffer>;  // output path -> binary data\n  data: Map<string, unknown>;   // shared plugin data store\n}\n```\nThe `data` map is the inter-plugin communication channel. Plugins write keyed data here (e.g., `\"taxonomy-tags\"`, `\"asset-manifest\"`, `\"dev-server-config\"`).\n\n### `PluginHooks`\n```typescript\ninterface PluginHooks {\n  beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n  transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile;\n  afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n}\n```\nThree lifecycle hooks, all optional. `transformContent` receives a single file and must return the (possibly transformed) file.\n\n### `Plugin`\n```typescript\ninterface Plugin {\n  name: string;\n  version: string;\n  dependencies: string[];  // names of plugins this depends on\n  hooks: PluginHooks;\n}\n```\nEach plugin has a name, version, a list of dependency plugin names (used for topological sorting), and hooks.\n\n### `Template`\n```typescript\ninterface Template {\n  name: string;\n  render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Build Engine (`/workspace/src/core/engine.ts`)\n\nThe `BuildEngine` class is the heart of the system:\n\n**State**: An array of `Plugin[]` and a `Map<string, Template>`.\n\n**`registerPlugin(plugin)`**: Pushes a plugin onto the array.\n\n**`registerTemplate(template)`**: Stores a template by name.\n\n**`resolvePluginOrder()`**: Performs a topological sort (depth-first) on the plugin dependency graph.\n- Throws `\"Circular dependency detected: ${name}\"` if a cycle is found.\n- Throws `\"Missing dependency: ${name} requires ${dep}\"` if a dependency is not registered.\n- Returns plugins in dependency-first order.\n\n**`build(files)`**: The main pipeline, which proceeds in four phases:\n1. **beforeBuild hooks** -- called in topological order on the `BuildContext`.\n2. **transformContent hooks** -- for each plugin (in order), iterates all files and replaces `ctx.files` with the transformed array.\n3. **Template rendering** -- for each file, looks up `file.template` (default: `\"default\"`) in the templates map, renders it passing content + merged metadata. Output stored as `\"${file.slug}.html\"` in `ctx.output`. Falls back to raw content if no template matches.\n4. **afterBuild hooks** -- called in topological order.\n\n**`getPlugins()`** and **`getTemplates()`**: Return shallow copies for inspection.\n\n---\n\n## Templates (`/workspace/src/core/templates.ts`)\n\nTwo factory functions:\n\n**`createDefaultTemplate()`**: Returns a template named `\"default\"` that renders a full HTML page with `<article>`, `<h1>`, optional `<time>`, and `<div class=\"content\">`.\n\n**`createListTemplate()`**: Returns a template named `\"list\"` that renders a simpler HTML page with `<h1>` and `<div class=\"list\">`.\n\n---\n\n## Core Index (`/workspace/src/core/index.ts`)\n\nRe-exports everything: `BuildEngine`, `createDefaultTemplate`, `createListTemplate`, and all types.\n\n---\n\n## Tests Analysis\n\n### Core Tests (`/workspace/tests/core.test.ts`) -- 15 tests\n\nTests the `BuildEngine` directly:\n1. **Registers plugins** -- plugin appears in `getPlugins()`.\n2. **Registers templates** -- template appears in `getTemplates()`.\n3. **Builds with default template** -- output contains DOCTYPE, title, content, site title.\n4. **Builds with list template** -- output contains `<div class=\"list\">`.\n5. **Raw content fallback** -- no template match yields raw content.\n6. **beforeBuild hook** -- verifies hook is called.\n7. **transformContent hook** -- verifies file content is transformed (uppercased).\n8. **afterBuild hook** -- verifies hook is called.\n9. **Dependency order** -- plugin B depends on A; order resolves to [A, B].\n10. **Circular dependency** -- throws error.\n11. **Missing dependency** -- throws error.\n12. **Multiple transforms in order** -- content appends `[first]` then `[second]`.\n13. **Shared data store** -- `ctx.data.set('key', 'value')` persists.\n14. **File metadata retained** -- metadata, date, tags survive the build.\n15. **Empty file list** -- output and files are empty.\n\n---\n\n### Plugin Tests (8 files, ~60 tests total)\n\nEach test file imports a factory function (`createXxxPlugin`) from `../../src/plugins/xxx.js` and exercises its hooks.\n\n#### 1. `markdown-ext.test.ts` (8 tests) -- `createMarkdownExtPlugin()`\n- **Hook used**: `transformContent`\n- Converts markdown to HTML (expects `<h1>`, `<strong>`).\n- **Footnotes**: `[^1]` syntax becomes `<sup><a href=\"#fn-1\">1</a></sup>`. Footnote definitions render in `<section class=\"footnotes\">` with `<li id=\"fn-1\">`.\n- **Admonitions/containers**: `:::note`, `:::warning`, `:::tip` blocks become `<div class=\"admonition admonition-note\">` etc.\n- Preserves existing HTML.\n- Handles empty content.\n\n#### 2. `asset-pipeline.test.ts` (8 tests) -- `createAssetPipelinePlugin()`\n- **Hook used**: `transformContent`\n- Rewrites `src=\"./image.png\"` to `src=\"/assets/image.png\"` and `href=\"./doc.pdf\"` to `href=\"/assets/doc.pdf\"`.\n- Leaves absolute URLs unchanged.\n- Generates `ctx.data['asset-manifest']` as `{ assets: string[] }` containing discovered filenames.\n- Accumulates assets across multiple files.\n- Does not double-process already-rewritten `/assets/` URLs.\n- No-op for content without 